// Should be used in conjuction with: "Debounce" Stop

// ================================================================================================

// This pair of nodes prevents actions taking place within too short a period defined by variable
// debounceMillisec in '"Debounce" Stop' node.

// Example use case... Back Garden Lights 
// Without the 'debounce' nodes:
//  1. Big Timer turns on lights at randomised offset at dusk everyday
//  2. This updates the HA Helper nput_boolean in Home Assistant to reflect current state of lights
//  3. The input_bool toggle update is detected by Node Red as a state change and triggers an 'on
//     override' message to be sent to the Big Timer node.
//     The lights stay on but the 'on override' message is treated as a manual override and Big
//     Timer will stay on until the next scheduled timer trigger which is turning the lights off
//     at the specified time - not an obvious issue but it removes the randomised offset for the
//     off timer.
//  4. When the un-randomised off messageis sent by Big Timer, it gaain updates the HA Helper
//     toggle in HA and this again is detected as a state change by Node Red and triggers an 'off
//     override' to be sent to Big Timer. This causes Big Timer to keep the lights off until the 
//     next scheduled on trigger i.e. it again removes the randomisation of turning the lights on.
//  5. Without the debounce nodes, we get two on messages every time the lights are turned on and
//     off (unless turned on/off by the HA toggle).

// It is also generally 'cleaner' and more sensible to avoid creating code or automation 'loops'.
// We ould easily get into the position where we accidentally create an infinite loop (e.g. if a
// flow toggles a HA input_boolean and that is state change is detected and triggers the same
// flow).

// ================================================================================================

// Set flow var to track last trigger time for debouncing - must have unique flow var names for
// each set of debounce nodes in the same flow.
// Update flow.get var name in '"Debounce" Stop' node to match this.

flow.set('debounceNode', new Date());

// ************** DEBUG (must come before 'return') **************
if (global.get('debug') == true) {
    node.warn("Debounce - Start Node @ " + flow.get('debounceNode') );
}
// ****

return msg;

